-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
(Question: How long would it take to get X item (a fully-aug'd BP for a melee) (cost=4,455 LDoN points).)<br>
Answer: Roughly 90 hours. (guessing)<br>
<br>
4500 LDoN points is, most likely, 88 missions on Normal difficulty, earning 51 points per win, granting you 4488 points.<br>
<br>
Each mission takes a decent chunk of time - I am NOT sure on the average amount, I usually take note of &quot;time left&quot; but not the total time elapsed start-to-finish.  You'll need to find a group, get a mission, get to the dungeon, buff, do your mission (and any secondary-missions once your adventure is complete, like named mobs, &quot;I need 6% to ding&quot;, etc), get back to the camp, sell, split, and start over again (possibly recruiting people as you go).  My estimate is just over an hour per mission, which may be overly high.<br>
<br>
Anyone with better data on average mission times (including outside-the-dungeon) step up!<br>
<br>
-----------------<br>
Personally, While I admire LDoN for offering non-raiders a chance to gear up, I do not see ANYTHING that I would actually wear at the shops, even fully augmented.  Granted, there is some stuff I would use that is from RAIDS or rare drops from HARD missions perhaps, but my LDoN points will probably all go to enhancing gear I get outside the dungeon.<br>
<br>
For instance, my hardest piece of gear to upgrade raiding right now is probably my Breastplate:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Chestplate of Vindication <br>
AC: 45, STA: +15 HP: +100<br>
SV FIRE: +15 SV DISEASE: +15 SV COLD: +15 SV MAGIC: +15 SV POISON: +15<br>
Effect: Aura of Battle (Worn), Slot 1, Type 7 (open)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The best LDoN upgrade for me would probably be:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Incorporeal Chain of the Specter  (1492)<br>
AC:61, Str:13, Dex:11, Wis:10, HP:100 (or 112), Mana:100<br>
FR:12, CR:12, PR:12<br>
type1: (Used for a +12 hp aug or +7 resist aug, both DROPPED)<br>
type2: (open)<br>
type3: Shiny Sandstone of Reconstruction (510)<br>
          Effect: Regeneration V (Worn)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
TOTAL: 2002 LDoN points.<br>
<br>
LDoN BP = +16AC, +11 Dex, +10 Wis, +100 Mana, NEGATIVE 39 Resists.  Plus 3 hp/tick regen, minus 10 attack, Plus one Type 1 slot (12hp/+7resist). <br>
<br>
In my opinion, a modest AC upgrade, minor stats, mana, and HP regen are not worth the expense.  I'm TEMPTED to swap the Regen V for Burning Affliction IV (another 640 points), but this aug could go in ANY type 3 slot (regen5 is only CHEST), and it would appear that I'm spending 3000 points just to get a focus effect that Sony added in to &quot;balance&quot; classes.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOTES:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
Some Ability-score stats are not included (i.e. Strength, Stamina) since they are MAXXED with self-buffs.  DEX is included even though I am 6 points away without Primal Essence/etc and will likely be maxxed with my next gear upgrade anyway.<br>
<br>
I am not filling the type 7 or type 2 slots in this example since either would just be filled with a +40hp aug for 1150 points (they have the same worth).<br>
<br>
I could sacrifice the 40hp on the LDoN BP to gain +25 resists for the same cost, but this seems ultimately less benificial.<br>
<br>
The two best &quot;any&quot; slot resist augs (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=24877" target="top">+8 poison, +8 disease</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=24935" target="top">+5 fire, cold, and magic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, both 663 points), are not included because as 'ANY' slot items, both will probably go on current gear (earrings!).<br>
<br>
IN SUM:  LDoN is great for gearing up non-raiders or offering casual raiders a place to gear up while exp'ing, but for the hardcore player only serves to enhance existing gear.<br>
<br>
And I'm STILL pissed about how hard it is to get Burning Affliction IV, even with the addition of the LDoN (type 3) aug (1150 pts). <p><br>
