<br>
2.  You compared BP's which is a bad point of comparison.  The Vindi BP is a way too good for how easy it is to get from a mob that is almost always up.  Even with this item though, the end LDoN BP, would be about 100 more mana, 40 more hp and a better effect.  That's significantly better than the Vindi BP.  I know that there are currently 2 FE clerics, one of them a long time member, wearing the LDoN plate BP fully augmented.  The non chest pieces are even better since it's often hard to find good non chest pieces.  Again, you compared one specific item that is rather unique, a 100hp BP with an effect that's found on an easy to kill, easy to find spawned mob.  That's not true of most slots.<br>
<br>
3.  You forgot to mention focus effects which are hard to find on non high end raid level gear but which the LDoN merchant bought gear offers non raiders.  For example, damage focuses, spell haste and mana preservation are all available on good stat / hp / mana items instead of having to sacrifice stats to get the same effects on things like ornate.  Your LDoN chain BP for example could have extended detrimentals or range focus added to it, making it far better than Vindi BP.<br>
<br>
4.  LDoN hard drops items that are an upgrade to many people.  These are dropped items, not merchant bought and you'll see them on people in even the highest end raiding guilds.<br>
<br>
5.  Depending on loot system, the LDoN items are a great way for people in high end raiding guilds to fill missing or weak slots with good gear without reducing their loot claiming ability.  FE for example is on a points system.  An FE member might choose to fill a weak slot with LDoN gear, which is pretty close to elemental quality, rather than spend points on claiming raid dropped gear in order to save up for other items.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'm currently wearing 1 dropped item from LDoN hard adventures and contemplating getting the int caster gloves from the MM merchant.  When fully augmented, they would be better for me than any other choice I could make, including PoTime gear.<br>
<br>
So LDoN has quite a bit to offer hard core raiders in any guild, besides just augments to upgrade existing gear.  And, no offense, but looking at your gear, I would say LDoN has quite a bit to offer for you too.  Not sure if you understand the situation currently in the elementals on Morell Thule, but your chance of personally seeing a large amount of elemental gear in the next few months is somewhere below my odds of winning the nobel peace prize.  So you could gear up quite nicely in LDoN and make yourself a far more effective shaman.<br>
<br>
Your primary item blows and should be replaced.<br>
Your boots are outdated and should be replaced.<br>
Your belt is outdated and should be replaced.<br>
Your non PoE A bracer is not fit for my level 30 rogue twink and needs to be replaced.<br>
Your sleeves need to be replaced.<br>
Your solstice earring needs to be replaced.<br>
Your rings could use an improvement.<br>
<br>
You may get boots, sleeves and bracer at some point.  Chain elemental patterns are common and rot frequently although your guild doesnt do many elemental targets.  Odds of ring, belt, earring and primary upgrades are hovering somewhere below my odds of developing tact and empathy.  <br>
<br>
By the way, I notice you're working on the Seru earring quest.  The work involved with that one is far more than the work you would do to get yourself a nice LDoN earring with a far better effect than Acumen.<br>
<br>
